summary: Okay, but if Diana Prince lives in Paris... and Villanelle lives in Paris... and Ratatouille lives in Paris... Crack!AU where...
body:
Okay, but if Diana Prince lives in Paris… and Villanelle lives in Paris… and Ratatouille lives in Paris…

Crack!AU where Villanelle sends Eve to La Ratatouille for a secret date in true Villanelle fashion, and Diana and Isabel just happen to be dining there that night (mostly because Diana is friends with all the rats and likes saying hello to them), and when Eve comes in and sees Villanelle, they have a “dinner incident” (in true Villaneve fashion), and that’s the story of how Wonder Woman and Dr. Poison meet Eve Polastri and Oksana Astonkova.

title: ...slay
body:
In today’s crusade, get ready to slay another #EmmyNominee with #KillingEve…

I admit, it felt like a crime that “Killing Eve,” one of the best new shows on television only received one Emmy nod (for Sandra Oh who absolutely deserves it), but this show as a whole is WAY too good to just award one small part of it, even if she is the title character.

I mean, Jodie Comer, as killer-for-hire Villanelle is equal parts terrifying and sweet, and that is not an easy balance to…

title: 4YE's Emmys 2018 Winner Wishlist Roundtable: Who Will Be Taking Home The Golden Girl?
body:
4YE’s Emmys 2018 Winner Wishlist Roundtable: Who Will Be Taking Home The Golden Girl?

Television’s golden night is almost upon us.

The 2018 Emmy Awards are this weekend, much to the delight of TV fans everywhere. There are a lot of first timers who are up for awards this year, and a lot of our faves here at 4 Your Excitement are also up for awards.

With the awards a few days away, we thought we would pick who we would like to see win one of the highly coveted Emmys up for grabs…
